CREATIVE CYPHER is showing Geeta's Guide To Moving On in their second web series showcase. Creative Cypher is a content development group based in Chicago. They focus on multiculturalism, diversity, and accessibility in new local web series. Join us on September 15th, 7:30 p.m. at Chicago Filmmakers! You can watch the season 1 trailer here!
Inside the complex process through which TV shows get made! #Netflix

Hollywood's belief that "the pool is wide but not deep" re: writers who aren't white and male is both true and not. 

TRUE - The pool is wide. Yet after excluding people for decades they will not have the "right credits" and work history to meet the standards set at a time of exclusion. 

FALSE - The pool is not deep. There are tons of great writers out there, but they have to be developed, cultivated, invested in. There are playwrights, novelists, poets, indie filmmakers and artists in other genres who have stories tell. But diversity programs aren't enough because it's not a real shot. People need funding and training to tell their own stories. Without funding for production, diversity talk is just lip service. 

Thankfully, OTV is here to help! Inquire within.
